    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-09-07T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-09-07T09:00:00-05:00" n="430"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d430">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.3227/9–746: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pawley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-09-07T11:00:00-03:00"
                            >September 7, 1946—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 7—10:33 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1570. For Norton and <gloss target="#t_CAB1">CAB</gloss> from Landis. Agreement
                        signed.<note n="88" xml:id="d430fn88">TIAS No. 1900, September 6,
                        1946.</note> No coastal route and Asuncion is out. Bermuda type. Brazilians
                    full accord with principles and will stick with them, in pending negotiations
                    Argentina, England and Portugal. [Landis.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Pawley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
